The published Configuration contract is a
singleton create/get surface. Reconcile binds
and rereads through
GetConfiguration(compartmentId) and creates only
when that root-compartment read confirms
absence.
CreateConfiguration is work-request-backed. The
runtime stores the create work request in
status.async.current, resumes through
GetZprConfigurationWorkRequest, recovers the
configuration identifier from work-request
resources, and then confirms state with
GetConfiguration.
No OCI update or delete operation is published.
Drift on zprStatus or tag maps is rejected,
compartmentId remains bind/create identity, and
Kubernetes delete performs local finalizer
cleanup only.
ACTIVE settles success, CREATING and UPDATING
requeue, FAILED remains terminal non-success,
and observed DELETED is treated as stale
identity or absence rather than managed delete
progress.
end note
